President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Arkansas due to severe storms and flooding that began on May 21, 2019. This declaration allows for Federal funding to assist individuals and communities affected by the disaster. The counties of Conway, Crawford, Faulkner, Jefferson, Perry, Pulaski, Sebastian, and Yell are eligible for assistance, which can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other recovery programs. Federal funding is also available for debris removal and emergency protective measures, including direct Federal assistance, in certain counties. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are eligible for cost-sharing funding. Jerry S. Thomas has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. The FEMA News Desk can provide further information.